dcterms:description: The MUTAG dataset contains 188 graph molecules labeled into two different classes according to their mutagenic properties, i.e., effect on the Gram-negative bacterium S. Typhimurium. It identifies several toxicophores - motifs in the molecular graph - that correlate with mutagenicity.
dcterms:title: Mutag

dcterms:description: The Alkane-Carbonyl dataset contains 1,125 molecular graphs categorized into two classes where an instance in the positive group indicates a molecule that contains an unbranched alkane and a carbonyl (C=O) functional group.
dcterms:title: Alkane-Carbonyl

dcterms:description: The DD dataset contains 1,178 protein graphs where nodes represent individual amino-acids and edges represent their spatial proximity. The task is to predict whether a given protein is an enzyme or not.
dcterms:title: DD

dcterms:description: The Proteins dataset contains 1,113 protein graphs where nodes represent secondary structure elements and edges indicate neighborhood in the amino-acid sequence or the 3D space. The task is to predict whether a given protein is an enzyme or not.
dcterms:title: Proteins
